      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(plugins): pin HTTP route registry during gateway bootstrap",
        "body": "Closes #94572\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nPlugin HTTP routes registered during bootstrap were invisible to the gateway because `registerPluginHttpRoute()` routes landed in a detached registry context, and `getPluginRouteRegistry()` couldn't find them.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded `pinActivePluginHttpRouteRegistry()` at bootstrap and runtime loader points, so `registerPluginHttpRoute()` routes land in the registry that `getPluginRouteRegistry()` can find.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\n$ npx tsx -e 'import { createPluginRegistry, pinActivePluginHttpRouteRegistry, registerPluginHttpRoute } from \"./src/plugins/...\"; ...'\n\nregistry.httpRoutes count: 1\nroute[0].path: /api/test-route\n```\n\nWith `pinActivePluginHttpRouteRegistry`, routes registered via `registerPluginHttpRoute()` appear in the visible registry that the gateway looks up.\n\n**Not tested:** End-to-end with a running gateway serving real HTTP requests.",
        "branch": "fix/issue-94572-plugin-http-routes",
